We have to refactor the whole cardmarket scraper logic and workflow.

Full implementation plan (phases, PR order, checklist): docs/cardmarket-scraper-refactor-plan.md

Main painpoints:
- The scraping process is really slow because the cf_clearance token cannot be extracted, because cardmarket do not load that for us.
This creates the issue that we have to run the scraping through chrome browser and we have to be careful with the rate limiting, because cardmarket is very strict with it. Based on experiences the card list scraping can be run stable only with 0.05 rps.
- The scraping process is really sensible, if there is a malfunction, the whole dataset will be corrupted. Currently we have spent 2 days with the card list scraping, there were some malfunctions, I had to stop the process, i have manually modified some files, and now there are so strong incconsistencies that we have start the scraping again from the beginning.
- The expansion seed list is a middleman for verifications, but we have to maintain it. If any problem occurs in it, we will have a validation error somewhere. We have to find a better maintainable solution.

What we want to achieve:
- Because the rate limiting is the borderline of the scraping process, we have to have a really stable scraping process. It should be resumable, it should be easily understandable and maintainable by any human being with basic programming knowledge.


